FAQs
Answers
What
is
I-Venture@ISB?
I-Venture@ISB
is
an
initiative
aimed
at
fostering
entrepreneurship
and
innovation
through
various
programs
and
support
mechanisms
at
Indian
School
of
Business
What
is
the
mission
of
I-Venture@ISB?

mission
of
I-Venture@ISB
is
to
support
and
nurture
startups
and
entrepreneurial
ventures
by
providing
mentorship,
funding,
and
a
supportive
ecosystem.

can
benefit
from
I-Venture@ISB?
Students,
entrepreneurs,
innovators,
and
startups
can
benefit
from
I-Venture@ISB.
Where
is
I-Venture@ISB
located?
I-Venture@ISB
operates
out
of
the
Indian
School
of
Business
campuses
in
both
Hyderabad
(known
as
DLabs)
and
Mohali
(known
as
AIC
ISB).

can
I
contact
I-Venture@ISB?
You
can
contact
I-Venture@ISB
via
their
official
website
i-venture.org
or
email
i-venture@isb.edu/contact@isbdlabs.org/contact@aicisb.org
